APC Comment.value: Chapman, APNI: 1285 (1991) listed 'Eucalyptus triantha var. carnea Domin' based on E. carnea R.T.Baker.  This is based on a misreading of Domin's text - he was commenting that Maiden had reduced R.T.Baker's E. carnea to a variety of E. acmenoides.  Eucalyptus triantha var. carnea Domin and var. triantha are therefore phantom names.  Occasional hybrids between E. carnea and 'E. signata' (=E. racemosa) are recorded (Hill, 1999).
